// The Waking Dream in Psychotherapy: Essay on the Regulating Function of the Collective Unconscious

== The Waking Dream (Directed Imagery)
_by Robert Desoille_

#inner-work[
  *The Three Movements:*
  1. *The Descent (Nigredo):* Turning attention into the shadow/unconscious to find "Stop Images" (psychic blockages). Corresponds to Calcination.
  2. *The Dawn (Albedo):* The transition from dark to light; images become transparent and luminous. Corresponds to Distillation.
  3. *The Day (Citrinitas/Rubedo):* Archetypal/Solar imagery. The integration of the higher self. Corresponds to Cohobation and the Stone.
]